<!--
Grid Cell Item for 9x9 Game Board with Separator Lines

IMPORTANT: The background drawable should be set programmatically based on cell position:
- For cells at column 2 or 5 (not 8): Use drawable with thick right border
- For cells at row 2 or 5 (not 8): Use drawable with thick bottom border
- For cells at both column (2,5) AND row (2,5): Use drawable with thick borders on both sides
- For cells at row 8: No bottom border
- For cells at column 8: No right border
- For cell at row 8, column 8: No borders

Border drawable options:
- @drawable/cell_border_normal - Normal thin borders on right and bottom
- @drawable/cell_border_thick_right - Thick right, thin bottom
- @drawable/cell_border_thick_bottom - Thin right, thick bottom
- @drawable/cell_border_thick_both - Thick borders on both right and bottom
- @drawable/cell_border_right_only - Right border only (for last row)
- @drawable/cell_border_bottom_only - Bottom border only (for last column)
- @drawable/cell_border_thick_right_only - Thick right border only (for last row)
- @drawable/cell_border_thick_bottom_only - Thick bottom border only (for last column)
- @drawable/cell_border_none - No borders (for last row, last column corner)

Example Kotlin code for RecyclerView Adapter:
```kotlin
fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
    val row = position / 9
    val col = position % 9

    val isThickRight = (col == 2 || col == 5)
    val isThickBottom = (row == 2 || row == 5)
    val isLastCol = (col == 8)
    val isLastRow = (row == 8)

    val backgroundDrawable = when {
        isLastRow && isLastCol -> R.drawable.cell_border_none
        isLastRow && isThickRight -> R.drawable.cell_border_thick_right_only
        isLastRow -> R.drawable.cell_border_right_only
        isLastCol && isThickBottom -> R.drawable.cell_border_thick_bottom_only
        isLastCol -> R.drawable.cell_border_bottom_only
        isThickRight && isThickBottom -> R.drawable.cell_border_thick_both
        isThickRight -> R.drawable.cell_border_thick_right
        isThickBottom -> R.drawable.cell_border_thick_bottom
        else -> R.drawable.cell_border_normal
    }

    holder.cellBackground.setBackgroundResource(backgroundDrawable)
}
```
-->
<FrameLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:id="@+id/cellContainer"
    android:layout_width="0dp"
    android:layout_height="0dp"
    android:layout_margin="0dp">

    <!-- Empty Cell Background (set programmatically based on position) -->
    <View
        android:id="@+id/cellBackground"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="@drawable/cell_border_normal" />

    <!-- Filled Cell Background -->
    <View
        android:id="@+id/cellFilled"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="@drawable/gradient_block_purple"
        android:visibility="gone" />

    <!-- Bomb Cell Container -->
    <FrameLayout
        android:id="@+id/cellBomb"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="@drawable/gradient_bomb_bg"
        android:visibility="gone">

        <!-- Bomb Timer Text -->
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/txtBombTimer"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_gravity="center"
            android:textSize="8sp"
            android:textColor="@color/white"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:text="5" />

    </FrameLayout>

</FrameLayout>